osts.\"", "\"SELLING PRICE PER 100 ML FOR BREAK-EVEN\":\"Selling price per 100 ml for break-even is the price at which the product must be sold to cover all costs and achieve zero profit or loss.\"", "\"FURTHER PROCESSING DECISION FACTORS\":\"Further processing decision factors include both financial and non-financial considerations, such as incremental revenue, costs, market acceptance, and health concerns.\"", "\"PERFUME PRODUCTION PROCESS\":\"Perfume production process refers to the steps and activities involved in creating the standard perfume, including blending aromatic oils with diluted alcohol and any additional processing.\"", "\"AROMATIC OILS\":\"Aromatic oils are the expensive, fragrant oils used in the production of perfume, which are blended with diluted alcohol to create the final product.\"", "\"DILUTED ALCOHOL\":\"Diluted alcohol is the primary component of the standard perfume, making up 99% of the product's volume.\"", "\"HORMONES FOR MALE AND FEMALE PERFUMES\":\"Hormones for male and female perfumes are the specific additives used to create the hormone-added versions of the perfume, designed to appeal to members of the opposite sex.\"", "\"LABOUR FOR FURTHER PROCESSING\":\"Labour for further processing refers to the additional workforce required to carry out the hormone-adding process for the new perfume variants.\"", "\"FIXED OVERHEAD RATE\":\"Fixed overhead rate is the predetermined rate used to allocate fixed overhead costs to products based on labour hours or other cost drivers.\"", "\"SALES PRICES FOR MALE AND FEMALE VERSIONS\":\"Sales prices for male and female versions refer to the prices at which the hormone-added perfumes for male and female customers are sold during the test month.\"", "\"SUPERVISOR'S ANNUAL SALARY\":\"Supervisor's annual salary is the yearly compensation paid to the supervisor, a portion of which is allocated to the hormone-adding process during the test month.\"", "\"EXTRA LABOUR FOR HORMONE-ADDED PERFUME\":\"Extra labour for hormone-added perfume refers to the additional workforce required to further process the perfume by adding hormones, beyond the labour needed for the standard product.\"", "\"NEW LABOUR AVAILABILITY\":\"New labour availability refers to the availability of additional skilled workers needed for the further processing of the perfume, which may be limited in the short term.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}